tive on United States Steel Corporation from $40.00 to $45.00 and gave the company a buy rating in a report on Tuesday, March 21st. United States Steel Corporation now has an average rating of "Hold" and an average target price of $28.87. TimkenSteel had 15 analyst reports since August 6, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. For now, AKS is the toast of Wall Street as its ABR stands at 2.50 with 3 out of 12 analysts rating the stock a buy. Analysts, on average, seem bullish as they suggest RES is worth $1.78 more, giving a target price of $23.36 a share. Timkensteel Corp (NYSE:TMST) has risen 34.77% since July 21, 2016 and is uptrending. AKS price is down almost -72.58% from its 52-week high price of $11.39 a share but is up about 41.36% from its 52-week low price of $3.87 a share. AK Steel Holding Corporation now has a P/E ratio of 25.58 and the market cap is 2.08B. The share price has moved forward from its 20 days moving average 3.39% and positively from its 50 days moving average 7.84%.
